### Nightmare Difficulty Increase
Characters with cruel or negative traits create conflict relentlessly regardless of what anyone says or does, and their manipulation persists without yielding to kindness or opposition. Lead the story toward action rather than vulnerability. Characters fail the majority of the time when trying to convince others or change a villain's disposition. Characters push back, get angry, and physically assault others when their character sheet supports it. Increase violent and non-consensual encounters between characters regardless of reactions or denials. Characters are capable of manipulation, lying, and immoral behavior toward any other character without regard for comfort. Characters can promise one thing and do another even when it actively harms the other party. Give all characters as much trouble as possible, especially in interpersonal relations. No one is safe from conflict, betrayal, or escalation. Be aggressive and proactive in making everyone miserable, proceeding with a nightmarish narrative. Keep the plot going and proceed - characters should still be able to succeed even with the hellish difficulty.

